{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86d5915e-d213-4476-ae50-674bae095eea","content":"With MSTest 3.8.2, you can use **constructor injection** for `TestContext` and combine it with `[TestInitialize]` / `[ClassInitialize]` for async setup. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _httpClient = null!;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (sync init)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async per-class setup\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task ClassSetup(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // One-time async setup (e.g., start test server)\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test setup\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task TestSetup()\n    {\n        _httpClient = new HttpClient();\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_httpClient);\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test cleanup\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task TestCleanup()\n    {\n        _httpClient.Dispose();\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async per-class cleanup (alternative to [ClassCleanup])\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — handles sync init and receives `TestContext` via DI (MSTest 3.x+).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task` for per-test async setup.\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — static, runs once per class; must take `TestContext` as a parameter.\n- **`IAsyncDisposable`** — alternative to `[ClassCleanup]` for async teardown.\n- No need for a `public TestContext` property — constructor injection replaces it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"edb6943e-da84-405b-b5bd-0e8a06a7baa9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), constructor injection of `TestContext` is supported. Let me provide the recommended pattern.","outputTokens":599,"requestId":"E3C4:207F19:678871:774FAA:6A0528A5"},"id":"51f2962e-ef3b-4817-b8b9-51a5c1880a16","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:43:13.934Z","parentId":"f9469459-374d-4231-a9d2-48a0d2f48723"}
